beginning around 1880

00:08:37.260 --> 00:08:40.340
and this was a key
technological breakthrough

00:08:40.340 --> 00:08:47.840 position:56%
as well oil is transported from Baku
a couple hundred miles along the

00:08:47.840 --> 00:08:51.470
Caspian Sea to the mouth
of the Volga River.

00:08:51.470 --> 00:08:55.000
And from there it was
carried up the Volga by boat,

00:08:55.000 --> 00:09:02.500 position:56%
stopped in major cities [inaudible],
Saratov, Samara, Kazan, [inaudible]

00:09:02.500 --> 00:09:10.810
and then eventually made its way
either by river or later by train

00:09:10.810 --> 00:09:12.330
to Moscow and Saint Petersburg.

00:09:12.330 --> 00:09:17.160 position:56%
This is before the end of the 20th
century in very, very large amounts.

00:09:17.160 --> 00:09:22.920
